Java tip: Collectors.toMap() will throw an error if your keys collide. Always consider a merge function. #Java #Streams

Example:

❌ Throws: IllegalStateException: Duplicate key:

List<Integer> nums = Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 4);
Map<Integer, Integer> squares = nums.stream()
.collect(Collectors.toMap(
n -> n % 2,
n -> n * n
));

✅ Fix: merge duplicates by summing values:

Map<Integer, Integer> squaresMerged = nums.stream()
.collect(Collectors.toMap(
n -> n % 2,
n -> n * n,
Integer::sum
));

